<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="that-conj">that <strong><em>conj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ðæt/    美 /ðæt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.****</h4>
<ul>
<li>引导名词性从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Many people believe that higher education should be free because it is good for the economy.
很多人认为高等教育应该免费，因为它对经济发展有益。</p><footer>2010 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The trouble was that she had lost her passport.
麻烦的是她把护照弄丢了。</p><footer>人教⑧ – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The news that the plane had crashed made us sad.
飞机失事的消息让我们很难过。</p><footer>译林③ – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>That he lost the match surprised us.
他输了比赛，我们很吃惊。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The manager put forward a suggestion that we should have an assistant.
经理提出一个建议，我们应该招一个助理。</p><footer>2016 天津</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>引导状语从句，表示原因、目的、结果等：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Speak louder (so) that I can hear you.
大声点说，好让我听见。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What was the matter with him that he looked so unhappy?
出了什么事，他看起来这么不高兴？</p></div>

<ul>
<li>用于强调结构“it is / was ... that …”中：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It was in New Zealand that Elizabeth first met Mr Smith.
伊丽莎白是在新西兰初遇史密斯先生的。</p><footer>2008 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s not doing the things we like, but liking the things we have to do that makes life happy.
生活的快乐不在于做自己喜欢的事，而在于喜欢自己不得不做的事。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-that">in that</h3>
<p>1.<strong>在…这一点上；因为：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We all long for sincere friendship in that it can deeply influence our lives.
我们都渴望真诚的友谊，因为它对我们的生活会产生深刻的影响。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>In many ways, the education system in the US is not very different from <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ in the UK.  （2016 浙江改）  </li>
<li>The most pleasant thing of the rainy season is <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ one can be entirely free from dust.  （2016 北京改）  </li>
<li>It is often the case<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ anything is possible for those who hang on to hope.  （2016 江苏改）  </li>
<li>You are waiting at a wrong place. It is at the hotel<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ the coach picks up tourists.  （2016 天津改）  </li>
<li>I truly believe<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ beauty comes from within.  （2015 北京改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. that  2. that  3. that  4. that  5. that  </p></div>